article.headline: UNLV 89, Colorado St. 70
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Tre'Von Willis scored 21 points to lead UNLV past Colorado State 89-70 Saturday night. Willis, who had 14 first-half points, went 8-of-12 from the field. He also had six assists and five rebounds. Rene Rougeau added 14 points and six rebounds for the Rebels (19-6, 7-4). Oscar Bellfield had 13 points and six assists, while Joe Darger also had 13 points. UNLV shot 33-of-61 (54 percent) from the field. Marcus Walker led Colorado State (8-17, 3-8) with 18 points. The Rebels never trailed and shot 65 percent in the first half. UNLV led 51-34 at halftime after shooting 8-of-11 from 3-point range. The Rebels finished 11-of-22 (50 percent) from 3-point range.
